                <section id="bookings">
                    <h2>4. Bookings and reservations</h2>
                    <p>When you reserve a trip, you make a binding offer to purchase that trip on the terms shown at checkout. We confirm the reservation when we send you a confirmation email containing your reference number. Until that email arrives, no reservation exists, even if our website displays the trip in your cart.</p>
                    <p>Trips are sold on an inventory basis. We use atomic database operations so that two travelers cannot reserve the same final spot. If inventory runs out during your checkout, we will tell you immediately and your card will not be charged.</p>
                    <p>The trip details shown on our site (itinerary, included services, departure city) are accurate to the best of our knowledge. Minor changes (room category swaps, replacement guides, alternative excursions for safety reasons) may occur, and we will notify you if any change is material.</p>
                </section>

                <section id="pricing">
